Etymology : Named for the resemblance of this sponge to the flowers of the ‘bottlebrush’ (
Callistemon spp .
) trees.

Microscleres
: Isochelae tridentate unguiferate with short sharp alae (49.8–65.8 x 
2.4–6.5 µm
) (
Figure 22 A
); rare sigmas with slight torsion (35.9–100.0 x 
1.2–3.3 µm
) (
Figure 22 B
) (see individual specimen measurements in 
Table 13
).
